“I drive a big delivery van, and I do the job, and it should be done professionally, cleanly, and safely for my customers,” said Telles, who also volunteers with the Gig Workers Collective.
And the nature of companies like Instacart is such that their contracted workers are treated as being crucial and expendable all at once.
“Kroger and Giant and others are doing all of the things that Instacart workers are doing and that Instacart and Amazon say is too much,” Liz Shuler, secretary-treasurer of the AFL-CIO, explained to me over the phone.